WEBVTT

00:54.864 --> 00:56.999
I know. It's really,
really stupid.

00:58.667 --> 01:01.904
The rules say, oh, you can't
have bra straps showing.

01:02.604 --> 01:05.574
I think it's the stupidest
thing I've ever heard.

01:08.077 --> 01:09.011
Right?

01:10.412 --> 01:12.747
Like, no bra straps?
What's with that?

01:12.749 --> 01:15.718
Yes, thank you! I know.

01:16.753 --> 01:17.918
- You don't look ready to go.
- Stop it!

01:17.920 --> 01:18.921
Two minutes!

01:19.922 --> 01:21.454
Oh, I've got an unbelievably
busy day today.

01:21.456 --> 01:25.092
I'm meeting Roxy for coffee at nine,
and then I've got five houses to show.

01:25.094 --> 01:29.832
Everybody wants to sell,
but who can afford to buy at these prices?

01:34.369 --> 01:35.002
Hmm.

01:35.004 --> 01:36.636
- It's yummy.
- Hmm.

01:36.638 --> 01:37.974
I'm trying to unclog your heart.

01:38.573 --> 01:39.541
My heart is not clogged.

01:40.609 --> 01:42.408
You eat like a teenager.

01:42.410 --> 01:43.576
Let's face facts.

01:43.578 --> 01:44.812
Oh, come here.

01:44.814 --> 01:46.548
It's time for you to face facts.

01:47.116 --> 01:47.984
Okay?

01:49.618 --> 01:50.718
Face it.

01:50.720 --> 01:52.287
Louise!

01:52.889 --> 01:54.556
Hmm, you smell great.

01:54.957 --> 01:56.857
It's that perfume you
got me for my birthday.

01:56.859 --> 01:58.060
Oh, yeah? Good for me.

02:01.530 --> 02:02.430
Oh.

02:03.465 --> 02:05.431
All right. Let's go. Backpack.

02:05.433 --> 02:06.801
Okay, I'm getting it.

02:06.803 --> 02:08.702
- Will you take these, please?
- Yeah.

02:08.704 --> 02:09.638
Okay.

02:10.940 --> 02:12.438
Bye.

02:12.440 --> 02:14.010
Hey, Louise, laces.

02:34.462 --> 02:35.597
Goodbye to you.

02:37.700 --> 02:38.935
Yuck.

02:50.012 --> 02:50.980
Hello.

02:51.981 --> 02:52.915
Amigo!

02:54.516 --> 02:57.952
Rob's Cafe, yes, yes.
You read my mind.

02:57.954 --> 02:59.621
Could you give me
like a half an hour?

03:00.622 --> 03:03.858
Yeah, order me, I don't
know, the No. 2 special,

03:03.860 --> 03:06.026
over-easy bacon on the side,
and you know what?

03:06.028 --> 03:09.697
While you're at it, why don't you throw in
a neat little stack of buttermilk pancakes?

03:09.699 --> 03:10.831
How about that?

03:41.197 --> 03:42.229
Oh, hey.

03:42.231 --> 03:43.529
Hi.

03:43.531 --> 03:45.567
Oh, hey.

03:45.935 --> 03:48.202
- You look amazing.
- Thanks.

03:48.204 --> 03:49.638
Did you do something
to your hair?

03:50.039 --> 03:51.105
I washed it.

03:51.107 --> 03:52.505
Hmm, looks really good.

03:52.507 --> 03:54.143
- Thank you.
- So,

03:55.044 --> 03:55.945
can you tell?

03:59.648 --> 04:01.581
I'm pregnant.

04:01.583 --> 04:03.119
Oh, my God!

04:04.921 --> 04:09.890
I couldn't say anything until I was at least 12
weeks along but I finally heard the heartbeat.

04:09.892 --> 04:12.159
Oh, my God! That's so exciting.

04:12.161 --> 04:14.663
Actually, I should
say heartbeats.

04:15.131 --> 04:16.764
Twins?

04:16.766 --> 04:17.698
Triplets.

04:18.768 --> 04:21.268
I know! I know! I know! I
know! Oh, my God! Okay.

04:21.270 --> 04:24.238
I mean, I knew... I knew this was a
possibility because of the fertility drugs,

04:24.240 --> 04:26.943
but Nicky is shitting bricks.

04:27.575 --> 04:29.076
Therapist has to work
to calm him down.

04:29.078 --> 04:30.911
Oh, I didn't know
you saw a therapist.

04:30.913 --> 04:33.047
Ah, triplets,
I can't believe it.

04:33.049 --> 04:34.782
I'm gonna have a
house full of kids.

04:34.784 --> 04:37.084
I only going to have to
wreck my body one time.

04:37.086 --> 04:38.953
I mean, I'm just...
I'm over the moon.

04:38.955 --> 04:40.254
I've already hired
a nursery designer.

04:40.256 --> 04:41.188
Is it helping?

04:41.190 --> 04:42.723
Oh, God, I'm buying
everything in sight.

04:42.725 --> 04:44.091
No, I mean, the therapist.

04:44.093 --> 04:46.260
Why? You guys don't go?

04:46.262 --> 04:49.964
No, but I think maybe we should.

04:49.966 --> 04:50.931
Problems?

04:50.933 --> 04:53.267
It's mostly just money stuff.

04:53.269 --> 04:54.835
That's why I think I
need to get a new job.

04:54.837 --> 04:57.037
No, no, honey, you are married.

04:57.039 --> 04:59.073
It is the man's job
to make the money.

04:59.075 --> 05:00.007
Yeah, Bob doesn't care.

05:00.009 --> 05:02.745
He's fine with things
the way they are.

05:03.212 --> 05:06.481
He better care if he wants
to stay married to you.

05:16.993 --> 05:19.559
All right. Just play it half
speed from right here.

05:19.561 --> 05:22.830
That's good. All right. So, now,
let's keep... it's after this, time right,

05:22.832 --> 05:24.597
okay, stop, pause,
see? Right there.

05:24.599 --> 05:29.703
Do you see it? Run it back frame by frame,
frame by frame, slowly, a little bit further,

05:29.705 --> 05:32.973
and right there.
Look, they're dancing.

05:32.975 --> 05:34.308
See it? Polar bears dancing.

05:34.310 --> 05:37.211
Yeah. Ha? That's our cover.

05:37.213 --> 05:39.046
That's our cover. Print
that image. That's great.

05:39.048 --> 05:41.183
You must be
so happy. That's great.

05:41.851 --> 05:44.051
But... but back...
back to the house.

05:44.053 --> 05:47.021
So, Larry, I mean, I think it
checks all the boxes, right?

05:47.023 --> 05:49.857
It... it, you know, it's got
the-the pool, the Jacuzzi,

05:49.859 --> 05:52.228
yeah, and it's great
for entertaining.

05:52.928 --> 05:54.263
Oh, can you hold on one second?

05:55.597 --> 05:57.833
Larry, I need one second.
I'll be right back.

05:58.968 --> 05:59.869
Hi.

06:00.635 --> 06:01.835
Yeah.

06:01.837 --> 06:05.007
No, no, I'm... I'm... I'm waiting
right here for you. Yeah.

06:07.143 --> 06:11.247
Uh, no, I can't come
back at seven tonight.

06:14.350 --> 06:18.687
No, no, no, no, it's fine. These things
happen. We... we'll reschedule it.

06:19.088 --> 06:21.123
You have a great audition, okay?

06:21.991 --> 06:23.625
Good luck! Bye.

06:26.228 --> 06:28.896
Larry, it's me, I'm back.
Thanks for holding. Okay.

06:28.898 --> 06:32.600
I think that if you want the house,
you're gonna have to make an offer.

06:34.703 --> 06:35.704
Hello, Larry?

06:45.247 --> 06:45.915
Ugh!

06:47.783 --> 06:49.952
- I hate real estate.
- Uh-oh.

06:54.190 --> 06:56.390
- What the heck!
- It will get better.

06:56.392 --> 06:58.692
I don't know, maybe
it's just a midlife thing.

06:58.694 --> 07:00.863
Life is just...

07:02.331 --> 07:03.665
Maybe you should get a new job.

07:04.834 --> 07:06.467
I like my job.

07:06.469 --> 07:10.206
Of course you do, and that's what I love
about you. You're so easily pleased.

07:11.273 --> 07:14.775
I want a break
from all the drudgery.

07:14.777 --> 07:19.046
I mean, I want
my life to expand.

07:19.048 --> 07:20.314
Yes, I know... I know
what you mean.

07:20.316 --> 07:22.282
- You do?
- Yeah, I do. I do.

07:22.284 --> 07:23.684
- You do?
- I do. I do. I do.

07:23.686 --> 07:25.786
That's why I think
that if we had a baby...

07:25.788 --> 07:30.157
I told you I don't
want a goddamn baby.

07:30.159 --> 07:34.797
We must have been insane not to
resolve this before we got married.

07:35.164 --> 07:40.868
Huh! Baby? Yeah, a baby! Who's gonna take care
of the baby and all the stuff for the baby

07:40.870 --> 07:42.037
and everything like that?

07:44.140 --> 07:48.709
Guess what? Roxy's
pregnant with triplets.

07:48.711 --> 07:52.946
In your wildest dreams you cannot imagine
the torture the triplets would be,

07:52.948 --> 07:55.217
and our marriage
would snap like a twig.

07:55.851 --> 07:59.219
She and Nick are in some kind of therapy
like marriage counseling or something.

07:59.221 --> 08:00.721
Oh, Jesus.

08:00.723 --> 08:02.091
I think we should try it.

08:03.359 --> 08:05.325
It doesn't mean that there's
something wrong with us.

08:05.327 --> 08:08.328
It just means that we want to
understand each other better.

08:08.330 --> 08:10.733
It... it's totally normal.

08:11.167 --> 08:14.301
It may be totally normal,
but why do we need it?

08:14.303 --> 08:17.237
Because we do,
because it's a good idea.

08:17.239 --> 08:22.910
We're fine the way we are,
and you talk about money issues, right?

08:22.912 --> 08:28.248
We're just... we're gonna pay to... to
invite a complete stranger into our lives?

08:28.250 --> 08:34.790
Well, we could, for example,
get a little help with the baby question.

08:36.225 --> 08:38.727
I mean, couldn't
we at least try it?

08:39.828 --> 08:42.331
It could change
our lives, right?

08:44.333 --> 08:48.037
I'm against it, but... but

08:48.971 --> 08:53.106
if it'll make you happy, I'll
try it once to make you happy.

08:53.108 --> 08:54.508
You are such a wonderful man.

08:54.510 --> 08:55.878
Oh.

08:57.513 --> 08:58.714
Hmm.

08:59.848 --> 09:02.349
If we hurry, we got some time
before Louise gets home.

09:02.351 --> 09:03.984
I don't need much time.

09:05.554 --> 09:07.054
Mom!

09:07.056 --> 09:08.422
What?

09:08.424 --> 09:10.290
I need more time than that.

09:36.051 --> 09:37.186
Hi.

09:37.553 --> 09:40.187
How are you?
Traffic was stupid.

09:40.189 --> 09:41.255
It was.

09:41.257 --> 09:43.557
Yeah, yeah, terrible.

09:47.296 --> 09:48.197
Welcome.

09:49.398 --> 09:51.300
I'm Judy Small.
Please come in.

10:00.342 --> 10:05.114
So the best way to begin is for you to
tell me a little bit about why you're here.

10:09.518 --> 10:10.352
Um,

10:11.487 --> 10:12.988
I guess

10:15.557 --> 10:19.928
I just really want
our marriage to be

10:20.929 --> 10:22.431
the real thing.

10:24.400 --> 10:26.566
You think it isn't
the real thing?

10:26.568 --> 10:29.403
No, I... I didn't... no,
I didn't mean that.

10:29.405 --> 10:31.905
I... I just... um...

10:31.907 --> 10:37.212
For whatever reason I think
I just... I don't feel satisfied.

10:38.314 --> 10:39.548
Why do you think that is?

10:41.417 --> 10:42.451
I don't know.

10:44.887 --> 10:48.924
I met my first husband
when I was in college.

10:50.125 --> 10:54.528
We fell in love,
and we got married,

10:54.530 --> 11:00.235
and we had Louise,
and one day I woke up to a ringing phone

11:01.070 --> 11:02.371
and he was dead.

11:04.206 --> 11:08.310
He was out fishing at
night with his friends and

11:10.512 --> 11:13.349
he fell overboard and
was killed by the propeller.

11:16.452 --> 11:17.486
I am sorry.

11:18.620 --> 11:22.690
For five years I took
care of Louise all by myself.

11:22.692 --> 11:24.692
I made all the money.

11:24.694 --> 11:28.564
I paid all the bills, and
I took the garbage out,

11:29.565 --> 11:31.867
and I guess I just-

11:33.469 --> 11:36.136
I kind of want to
be taken care of.

11:36.138 --> 11:40.275
- And you feel that Bob doesn't take care of you?
- No, I... I mean, yes.

11:41.577 --> 11:42.945
I love Bob.

11:43.312 --> 11:44.279
I just-

11:45.147 --> 11:47.447
I think maybe I want
more than he does.

11:47.449 --> 11:49.983
He... he doesn't seem to
care about money at all.

11:49.985 --> 11:51.251
No, I care.

11:51.253 --> 11:53.989
I care. It's just that money has
never been that important to me.

11:56.125 --> 12:00.295
I just want to be happier I
guess, you know, I want... if

12:01.230 --> 12:07.136
true happiness exists, and I think it does,
I mean, I definitely tasted it with Bob.

12:07.737 --> 12:12.641
If happiness is out
there, I just really want it.

12:14.276 --> 12:15.177
I see.

12:19.381 --> 12:21.250
Why are you here today, Bob?

12:24.119 --> 12:24.953
Well,

12:25.889 --> 12:28.123
yeah, Susan pretty
much dragged me here.

12:35.063 --> 12:38.733
Tell me, what is it
you do professionally?

12:38.735 --> 12:42.068
Oh, um, I'm the Head of
Programming at The Nature Channel.

12:42.070 --> 12:43.203
I love that channel.

12:43.205 --> 12:44.137
You do?

12:44.139 --> 12:48.375
Yes, I find animals
just so fascinating.

12:48.377 --> 12:50.343
Oh, well, I just uh...
you're going to love this.

12:50.345 --> 12:52.948
I just finished this special
about polar bears.

12:53.382 --> 12:55.517
Just remarkable animals.

12:56.185 --> 12:57.150
Remarkable.

12:57.152 --> 12:58.786
Well, that's splendid.

12:58.788 --> 13:03.959
I just want our marriage to be the best
it can be, to be as strong as it can be.

13:04.426 --> 13:06.595
Is there something
wrong with that?

13:07.229 --> 13:11.164
Do you have ideas about how I might
be able to help you in this regard?

13:11.166 --> 13:17.239
Well, yes, I mean there are a few
things, maybe one, or two, or three.

13:18.775 --> 13:23.310
First, there's the issue of, you
know, how we both feel about money,

13:23.312 --> 13:24.812
how much we need
to feel secure.

13:24.814 --> 13:26.112
- I think that's a big one.
- Hmm.

13:26.114 --> 13:29.249
And then there's the issue

13:29.251 --> 13:31.386
of whether or not
we have a baby.

13:32.254 --> 13:34.020
Mm-hmm.

13:34.022 --> 13:37.725
And then there's our family dynamic, you know,
Louise, my daughter, she's 13 years old

13:37.727 --> 13:40.761
and she's lovely.

13:40.763 --> 13:43.465
She's a blossoming
young woman, really, and

13:45.768 --> 13:47.737
lately I wonder

13:49.171 --> 13:51.304
if it's getting
complicated for Bob.

13:51.306 --> 13:52.207
What?

13:55.110 --> 13:56.643
What are you even
talking about right now?

13:56.645 --> 13:59.414
The other morning,
in the kitchen,

14:00.649 --> 14:04.019
I saw you looking at her.
She was in her underwear.

14:11.527 --> 14:12.492
Yeah.

14:12.494 --> 14:13.293
Yes.

14:13.295 --> 14:15.262
I see Louise.

14:15.264 --> 14:18.799
I'm not looking at her, not in the
way that you're implying at least.

14:18.801 --> 14:20.469
I can't even believe
you're saying this.

14:24.106 --> 14:29.442
You know what? I think... I think I'm a pretty
damn good stepfather, and a good husband...

14:29.444 --> 14:31.146
- Yes.
- too for that matter.

14:32.147 --> 14:33.315
I love Louise.

14:33.783 --> 14:35.484
I love Susan, but

14:36.618 --> 14:39.087
a comment like that,
that is just damn hurtful.

14:39.689 --> 14:41.089
It's damn hurtful.

14:45.260 --> 14:48.161
Perhaps Louise
should join us next week.

14:48.163 --> 14:49.631
If you think that's
helpful, yeah.

14:50.198 --> 14:51.066
I defer.

15:12.654 --> 15:15.723
So are you and Bob
getting a divorce?

15:15.725 --> 15:18.226
Oh, baby, of course not.

15:18.695 --> 15:20.730
- No.
- Well, then why are you seeing a shrink?

15:21.931 --> 15:25.733
- Never mind. Don't tell me.
- She sees lots of couples.

15:25.735 --> 15:28.401
Don't tell me that.
That's really gross.

15:28.403 --> 15:29.603
- Really, gross?
- Mm-hmm.

15:29.605 --> 15:32.207
- Oh, it's so gross.
- Yeah, it's disgusting.

15:33.342 --> 15:36.578
Listen, you are a very
important part of this family,

15:38.280 --> 15:41.784
and you are my favorite
person in the entire world

15:43.352 --> 15:46.754
so I want you to come
with us next time we see her.

15:46.756 --> 15:47.922
- No way.
- Yes.

15:47.924 --> 15:50.891
- No! No, I... I won't do it.
- You are going to see her.

15:50.893 --> 15:52.592
- No.
- Yes, you are.

15:52.594 --> 15:53.894
- Yes, you are.
- No.

15:53.896 --> 15:54.897
Yes!

16:00.803 --> 16:02.703
- <i>Se√±or.</i>
- Amigo.

16:02.705 --> 16:04.337
How are those polar
bears coming?

16:04.339 --> 16:06.239
Good, yeah, almost set to go.

16:06.241 --> 16:06.909
Great.

16:07.542 --> 16:09.309
Uh, you got a minute to talk?

16:09.311 --> 16:11.511
Yeah, yeah, yeah, no problem.

16:11.513 --> 16:12.280
What's up?

16:18.054 --> 16:23.492
Clarette got pink-slipped at Disney so she's
freaking out about finding a new job, and

16:24.226 --> 16:26.694
I don't exactly blame her
'cause times are tough.

16:26.696 --> 16:28.929
Yeah, I'm sorry
to hear that, man.

16:28.931 --> 16:34.300
Yeah, so our income just got cut in half, and
now she decides she wants to get married,

16:34.302 --> 16:36.536
and buy a place with a
swimming pool up in the hills.

16:36.538 --> 16:38.505
I thought you and
Clarette were married.

16:38.507 --> 16:41.343
No, just... just keeping house.

16:41.878 --> 16:44.312
Anyway, that's...
that's not why I'm here.

16:47.449 --> 16:50.318
Um, you know, Annabelle
Bernard down in accounting?

16:51.486 --> 16:54.287
Dark hair, great
legs, short skirt.

16:54.289 --> 16:55.890
Yeah, yeah, sure, Annabelle.

16:55.892 --> 16:58.326
We... we started this thing,

16:59.028 --> 17:00.728
you know, nothing serious.

17:00.730 --> 17:05.632
Just a couple of days a week at lunch, and
then yesterday she comes into my office,

17:05.634 --> 17:10.639
closed the door behind her, as soon as that
happens, man, my heart went through the floor

17:11.373 --> 17:16.911
'cause she's in love with me,
wants us to quit our jobs, move to Mexico.

17:16.913 --> 17:18.045
Seriously?

17:18.047 --> 17:18.848
Yeah.

17:20.449 --> 17:22.850
And... and I'll tell you what scares the
shit out of me. It's... it's not Clarette.

17:22.852 --> 17:24.651
I... I can handle Clarette.

17:24.653 --> 17:27.988
It's... with the world turned upside down these
days, all she has to do is point the finger

17:27.990 --> 17:29.355
and my ass is grass.

17:29.357 --> 17:31.859
Sexual harassment?
You think she'd do that?

17:31.861 --> 17:33.928
Nowadays? Come on.

17:33.930 --> 17:35.898
These women will do anything.

17:37.432 --> 17:39.566
Wow! Well, have you
tried talking to her?

17:39.568 --> 17:43.536
Have you ever tried talking to a woman
especially one that's pissed off at you?

17:43.538 --> 17:45.507
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

17:47.043 --> 17:47.810
Um-

17:52.414 --> 17:55.484
Um, do you want
me to talk to her?

17:56.085 --> 17:57.985
Oh, man, would you?

17:57.987 --> 17:59.689
Yeah, sure.

18:02.024 --> 18:03.556
You're a gentleman
and a scholar.

18:03.558 --> 18:04.557
No, it's my pleasure.

18:04.559 --> 18:05.828
- Thank you.
- For sure.

18:07.529 --> 18:10.998
Hey I'd love to stick around, but I got an
appointment across town I got to get to.

18:11.000 --> 18:13.466
- Job prospect?
- Yeah, no, no, no, no.

18:13.468 --> 18:14.467
Marriage counseling.

18:14.469 --> 18:15.770
- Ooh.
- Yeah.

18:15.772 --> 18:16.906
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

18:27.649 --> 18:28.718
It's okay to laugh.

18:29.118 --> 18:32.987
I just think this whole
thing is weird.

18:32.989 --> 18:37.524
Laughter can be very constructive
sometimes just for the release of it.

18:37.526 --> 18:41.697
I laugh between sessions,
alone, right here in my office.

18:44.934 --> 18:46.533
Oh, bless you.

18:46.535 --> 18:47.302
Thank you.

18:49.739 --> 18:50.639
There.

18:51.439 --> 18:51.941
Bingo!

18:53.475 --> 18:54.010
Hmm,

18:55.410 --> 18:56.545
one sneeze.

18:58.080 --> 19:03.650
If I didn't have my hankie, bacteria,
germs would've spread amongst us all.

19:03.652 --> 19:09.357
Think of your conflicts as germs,
left unchecked, without a hankie,

19:09.959 --> 19:14.128
they spread among you...
the three of you, living unit.

19:14.130 --> 19:17.033
I have never really felt
like a germ before.

19:19.135 --> 19:19.936
Well,

