Hello?

1:22:12.842 --> 1:22:13.874
It's Louise.

1:22:13.876 --> 1:22:14.777
Is Bob there?

1:22:17.680 --> 1:22:19.648
Well, do you know where he is?

1:22:20.582 --> 1:22:21.583
Never?

1:22:22.217 --> 1:22:23.285
Okay, bye.

1:22:24.954 --> 1:22:29.623
He never showed up at work even though he
had a meeting with the writer from Alaska.

1:22:29.625 --> 1:22:31.560
Something's definitely wrong.

1:22:33.662 --> 1:22:36.697
So much is wrong,
I don't even know where...

1:22:36.699 --> 1:22:40.701
Well, he... he... he could be in
jail, or bleeding to death somewhere.

1:22:40.703 --> 1:22:42.703
- Louise.
- Or else he could have a heart attack.

1:22:42.705 --> 1:22:44.805
- Don't say that.
- I'm sorry.

1:22:44.807 --> 1:22:46.941
I can tell you're
already freaking out.

1:22:46.943 --> 1:22:50.543
I'm not freaking out.
I'm just a little tired.

1:22:50.545 --> 1:22:52.614
I think we're better
off facing the truth.

1:22:53.649 --> 1:22:56.549
I'm having a very
painful realization.

1:22:56.551 --> 1:22:57.285
What?

1:22:59.822 --> 1:23:01.989
I still love Bob.

1:23:01.991 --> 1:23:05.327
Oh, my God. I thought
that's why you married him.

1:23:07.262 --> 1:23:11.899
It's crazy how easy it is to forget
how much someone means to you

1:23:11.901 --> 1:23:20.475
even if they've been a complete
reptile, all their fuck-ups and flaws.

1:23:21.978 --> 1:23:25.445
Oh, baby, if anything ever happened
to him I don't know if I...

1:23:25.447 --> 1:23:26.346
Mom, not now.

1:23:26.348 --> 1:23:27.482
Okay.

1:23:31.988 --> 1:23:34.554
I bet you it has something
to do with Judy Small.

1:23:34.556 --> 1:23:35.756
Judy Small.

1:23:35.758 --> 1:23:36.824
Judy Small.

1:23:36.826 --> 1:23:38.226
Judy.

1:23:42.364 --> 1:23:43.231
Judy?

1:24:00.783 --> 1:24:01.918
Filed a report.

1:24:03.385 --> 1:24:07.387
If we haven't heard from him in 24
hours, we'll just have to come back.

1:24:07.389 --> 1:24:08.756
Well, that's dumb.

1:24:08.758 --> 1:24:09.992
What if tomorrow is too late?

1:24:10.860 --> 1:24:13.326
I can't make you
a little cozier.

1:24:13.328 --> 1:24:15.328
- Can you help me out here, babe?
- Judy.

1:24:15.330 --> 1:24:16.396
Judy.

1:24:16.398 --> 1:24:18.598
- Judy.
- What? What?

1:24:18.600 --> 1:24:19.834
You can't do this.

1:24:19.836 --> 1:24:21.301
Judy, you can't do this.

1:24:21.303 --> 1:24:22.739
You can't keep me prisoner.

1:24:24.406 --> 1:24:25.474
Get it straight.

1:24:26.508 --> 1:24:28.075
I'm leaving tonight, and
you're coming with me.

1:24:28.077 --> 1:24:30.477
Maybe he's glad that he left me.

1:24:30.479 --> 1:24:31.580
He's not.

1:24:32.481 --> 1:24:35.482
Oh, God, I really don't want...

1:24:35.484 --> 1:24:37.584
When I saw them
naked on that couch...

1:24:37.586 --> 1:24:38.585
He... he is.

1:24:38.587 --> 1:24:40.386
All naked and crawled
up like two white dogs.

1:24:40.388 --> 1:24:41.055
Louise!

1:24:41.057 --> 1:24:42.959
Mom, you're gonna blow it!

1:24:44.026 --> 1:24:45.993
I think I'm blowing it.

1:24:45.995 --> 1:24:48.263
- What are you doing?
- No, you're not.

1:24:48.798 --> 1:24:50.865
I'm sorry!

1:24:50.867 --> 1:24:55.337
Susan and I came to you
because we needed your help.

1:24:55.905 --> 1:25:00.743
Every child wants a
grownup who will pretend

1:25:01.476 --> 1:25:03.713
so I'm gonna tell you
what we're going to do.

1:25:05.480 --> 1:25:10.519
We're going to drive, and then we're going to
fly, and then we're gonna head towards water

1:25:11.854 --> 1:25:21.329
because I see a white sail against
just the most ethereal blue sky.

1:25:23.099 --> 1:25:26.633
Mom, we need to go now
to Judy Small's office.

1:25:26.635 --> 1:25:27.768
Not planned.

1:25:27.770 --> 1:25:30.938
Hands on the wheel
and eyes on the road.

1:25:30.940 --> 1:25:31.806
Thank you.

1:25:31.808 --> 1:25:33.743
I know the fires in need.

1:25:34.609 --> 1:25:35.845
I know the truth.

1:25:36.813 --> 1:25:41.449
I know the truth but
Dr. Kingsley says

1:25:42.417 --> 1:25:45.888
human beings suffer from
reminiscences, Judith.

1:25:46.823 --> 1:25:49.792
You... you suffer from nothing.

1:25:50.827 --> 1:25:54.128
Somewhere there is
a human life for you.

1:25:54.130 --> 1:25:57.630
Judy, I love my wife.

1:25:57.632 --> 1:25:59.334
And yet

1:26:01.137 --> 1:26:03.338
I pretend you love me,

1:26:04.907 --> 1:26:06.709
and you must pretend the same.

1:26:08.811 --> 1:26:10.680
I'm calling 911.

1:26:11.147 --> 1:26:12.048
Come on, baby.

1:26:13.015 --> 1:26:14.382
Coming.

1:26:26.762 --> 1:26:28.595
We should break down the door.

1:26:28.597 --> 1:26:31.832
Yes. We need something.
We need like, um, like a hammer or-

1:26:31.834 --> 1:26:32.766
- Wait, go ask that guy.
- Okay.

1:26:32.768 --> 1:26:33.635
Ask him for help.

1:26:34.569 --> 1:26:35.568
Mom, money.

1:26:35.570 --> 1:26:36.770
You don't need money.

1:26:36.772 --> 1:26:38.504
- Okay.
- Bob!

1:26:38.506 --> 1:26:39.505
Susan!

1:26:39.507 --> 1:26:41.008
Judy!

1:26:41.010 --> 1:26:45.145
- Help!
- Shut up. Shut up. Shut up!

1:26:45.147 --> 1:26:47.715
- You need help?
- Yes, he... my husband is in there.

1:26:47.717 --> 1:26:49.515
- You sure he's in there?
- Yes, I'm positive. He's in there.

1:26:49.517 --> 1:26:50.853
- Please, just break the lock.
- Okay. Okay.

1:26:52.788 --> 1:26:54.021
I hear Bob.

1:26:54.023 --> 1:26:55.024
Shhh!

1:26:58.828 --> 1:27:01.130
- Okay, I got it.
- Okay. You stay.

1:27:03.165 --> 1:27:05.799
- Bob!
- Susan!

1:27:05.801 --> 1:27:06.499
Where's Bob?

1:27:06.501 --> 1:27:07.801
Mom! That's Judy. That's Judy.

1:27:07.803 --> 1:27:10.804
Hey, whoa, whoa. Where are you going?
Just relax, lady, okay?

1:27:10.806 --> 1:27:11.872
- Ahh.
- Gah, aw. God.

1:27:11.874 --> 1:27:13.140
Hey, hey, what's going on here?

1:27:13.142 --> 1:27:14.540
Help. Just let me go. Help.

1:27:14.542 --> 1:27:15.575
- Let her go, now.
- No, no, but no...

1:27:15.577 --> 1:27:17.978
What are you doing?
Don't let her go! Get her!

1:27:17.980 --> 1:27:19.547
- She just bit me, man. She's crazy.
- Go!

1:27:21.250 --> 1:27:22.018
Oh, my God.

1:27:27.555 --> 1:27:29.725
I was so scared.

1:27:33.262 --> 1:27:35.729
- I'm sorry.
- Susan, Susan, Susan, my Susan.

1:27:35.731 --> 1:27:36.431
Bob.

1:27:43.773 --> 1:27:45.039
No, stay back.

1:27:45.041 --> 1:27:45.906
I'm gonna jump.

1:27:45.908 --> 1:27:48.208
2546, we need a
jumper squad right away.

1:27:48.210 --> 1:27:49.712
- Hey, look.
- Mom.

1:27:52.048 --> 1:27:52.848
Judy!

1:27:58.721 --> 1:28:00.522
You okay? Yeah.

1:28:01.057 --> 1:28:02.790
Whoa, what are you doing?
You shouldn't be up here.

1:28:02.792 --> 1:28:03.791
- Stand down.
- It's okay.

1:28:03.793 --> 1:28:06.026
I know her. I know her.
It's okay. It's okay.

1:28:06.028 --> 1:28:07.462
She's my therapist.

1:28:10.800 --> 1:28:11.734
Judy.

1:28:12.201 --> 1:28:12.935
Judy.

1:28:14.236 --> 1:28:14.904
Hey.

1:28:17.605 --> 1:28:18.473
Hey, Bob.

1:28:19.041 --> 1:28:20.042
What are you doing?

1:28:23.112 --> 1:28:25.245
Now, come on. Come here.
Come here. Come here.

1:28:25.247 --> 1:28:26.514
This isn't you.

1:28:27.016 --> 1:28:27.717
No, come on.

1:28:28.284 --> 1:28:30.150
Come on, Judy.
You don't do this.

1:28:30.152 --> 1:28:31.887
Judy Small doesn't do this.

1:28:32.855 --> 1:28:33.990
No, you don't.

1:28:37.827 --> 1:28:39.095
Yeah, I've got you.

1:28:39.729 --> 1:28:41.831
Let me help you now. Come on.

1:28:42.732 --> 1:28:43.565
Yeah?

1:28:45.801 --> 1:28:48.037
Okay. Okay. Oh, oh, okay.

1:28:48.704 --> 1:28:50.304
I've got you. I've got you.

1:28:50.306 --> 1:28:51.173
Okay.

1:28:53.575 --> 1:28:54.176
Okay.

1:28:59.614 --> 1:29:00.548
Lover.

1:29:02.084 --> 1:29:02.985
Jewel.

1:29:27.810 --> 1:29:29.178
What are you doing home?

1:29:31.147 --> 1:29:32.580
I have bad news.

1:29:33.315 --> 1:29:34.250
What?

1:29:35.317 --> 1:29:36.285
I got fired.

1:29:38.988 --> 1:29:42.022
How can they fire you?
You have a contract.

1:29:42.024 --> 1:29:45.194
I know. I know. They're gonna buy
me out for 30 cents on the dollar.

1:29:46.128 --> 1:29:47.296
Well, what happened?

1:29:49.398 --> 1:29:52.667
There was this thing with...
with Reed and Walter,

1:29:53.269 --> 1:29:56.336
and I didn't tell you about it because
I wanted to wait until it was done

1:29:56.338 --> 1:29:59.940
so I could come to you and say,
here it is, here's the new deal.

1:29:59.942 --> 1:30:00.974
Here's the big money.

1:30:00.976 --> 1:30:02.311
Here's the new salary.

1:30:03.578 --> 1:30:07.750
And Beaver found out about it,
and told us to pack our bags.

1:30:10.820 --> 1:30:16.356
Look, Susan, I know how bad this
looks, but I'm gonna find another job.

1:30:16.358 --> 1:30:17.659
You don't have to worry.

1:30:20.963 --> 1:30:26.100
You've been fired and we
have no income to speak of,

1:30:26.102 --> 1:30:28.571
and almost no savings.

1:30:34.443 --> 1:30:35.377
But

1:30:39.448 --> 1:30:41.050
at least we have each other.

1:30:43.953 --> 1:30:45.387
Shit.

1:30:51.927 --> 1:30:52.928
Does that hurt?

1:30:53.329 --> 1:30:55.295
Not too much.

1:30:55.297 --> 1:30:57.297
- Good.
- Not anymore.

1:30:57.299 --> 1:30:58.834
Being a tough guy?

1:31:11.247 --> 1:31:14.715
If we hurry we still have time
before Louise gets home.

1:31:14.717 --> 1:31:15.684
Yeah.

1:31:29.832 --> 1:31:30.733
Hello?

1:31:32.234 --> 1:31:34.537
Oh!

1:31:38.407 --> 1:31:41.010
- That's weird.
- Yeah.

1:31:43.245 --> 1:31:44.947
You know what that means?

1:31:46.182 --> 1:31:47.915
Oh, God.

1:31:47.917 --> 1:31:49.318
So gross.

1:31:51.353 --> 1:31:53.487
They barely even
talk to each other.

1:31:53.489 --> 1:31:54.588
Eww.

1:31:54.590 --> 1:31:58.694
Aren't married people
supposed to do it at night?

